    "Note that: e iσ (T -T W ZW -Tσ -Tρ):= ∂[: -e iσ ∂(ρ + iσ):] so that, as far as the BRST charge is concerned, the stress tensor appearing in G + is the natural stress tensor of the AdS3 × S 3 part of the theory.",
